<p>The Asian Philosophy of Science Association (APSA) is a new organization dedicated to advancing research and teaching in philosophy of science in Asia.<span id="more-53097"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="wp-image-53104 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/asian-philosophy-of-science-association-1024x572.png" alt="" width="805" height="450" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/asian-philosophy-of-science-association-1024x572.png 1024w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/asian-philosophy-of-science-association-300x168.png 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/asian-philosophy-of-science-association-768x429.png 768w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/asian-philosophy-of-science-association-1536x858.png 1536w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/asian-philosophy-of-science-association-400x223.png 400w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/asian-philosophy-of-science-association.png 1812w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 805px) 100vw, 805px" /></p>
<p>The organization aims to promote dialogue and collaboration between philosophers of science in Asia, facilitate new research and pedagogy in philosophy of science, and offer a new communication platform between philosophers of science in Asia and other parts of the world.</p>
<p>APSA has a mailing list, runs a mentorship program, puts on events, lists professional opportunities, among other things. It will be holding the first of a series of biennial conferences in the summer of 2026.</p>
<p>APSA is run by an elected Governing Board with the support of an office based in Hong Kong. The inaugural office-holders are:</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">President: Chuang Liu (Fudan University)<br />
Vice President: Yafeng Shan (The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology)<br />
Treasurer: Nikolaj Jang Lee Linding Pedersen (Yonsei University)<br />
Membership Committee Co-chair: Young E Rhee (Dongguk University)<br />
Membership Committee Co-chair: Wei Wang (Tsinghua University)<br />
Media Committee Chair: Qiaoying Lu (Peking University)<br />
Outreach Committee Chair: Eugene Y. S. Chua (Nanyang Technological)</p>
<p>You can <a href="https://www.philsciasia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">learn more about APSA at its website</a>.</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/03/19/new-asian-philosophy-of-science-association/">New: Asian Philosophy of Science Association</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>